CIA Triad (also called AIC Triad) are the core fundamentals of security:
Confidentiality: prevent disclosure of information to unauthorized individuals. Some ways are encryption, access controls, two-factor authentication, etc.
Integrity: data is stored and transferred as intended. Information can't be modified without detection. Some ways are hashing, digital signatures, certificate, etc.
Availability: systems and networks must be able to run. Some ways are redundancy, building fault tolerant systems, patching, etc.
